│ THOUGHT                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ The user wants me to fix a crash in LLVM's Scalar Evolution analysis, which is triggered by the `simple-loop-unswitch` pass.                                                             │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The crash is an assertion failure: `isAvailableAtLoopEntry(Op, L) && "SCEVAddRecExpr operand is not available at loop entry!"` in `ScalarEvolution::getAddRecExpr`. This happens during  │
│ `ScalarEvolution::verify()`, which is called after `simple-loop-unswitch`.                                                                                                               │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The problem is that `simple-loop-unswitch` can create a situation where a `SCEVAddRecExpr` for a loop `L` has an operand that is not available at the entry of `L`. This violates a      │
│ fundamental invariant of `SCEVAddRecExpr`.                                                                                                                                               │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The reproducer shows a complex loop structure. The `simple-loop-unswitch` pass likely unswitches one of the loops based on the loop-invariant condition `%check = icmp eq ptr %p, null`. │
│ This transformation seems to be what exposes the bug in Scalar Evolution.                                                                                                                │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The assertion `isAvailableAtLoopEntry(Op, L)` checks if an operand `Op` of an `AddRec` for loop `L` is defined outside of `L` or is an `AddRec` for a loop containing `L`. The crash     │
│ indicates that after unswitching, an operand becomes loop-variant with respect to `L` in a way that `isAvailableAtLoopEntry` doesn't expect. Specifically, it's likely an `AddRec` for a │
│ loop that is no longer an outer loop of `L`.                                                                                                                                             │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The stack trace shows the crash happens inside `ScalarEvolution::verify()`, which calls `SCEVRewriteVisitor` to reconstruct the SCEV expressions. The assertion fails inside             │
│ `getAddRecExpr` when it's trying to build a new `SCEVAddRecExpr`.                                                                                                                        │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ A common cause for such issues is when a pass modifies the IR and invalidates SCEV information, but doesn't properly update or clear it. `simple-loop-unswitch` is a loop transform, and │
│ it's supposed to update SCEV.                                                                                                                                                            │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The assertion is in `ScalarEvolution.cpp`. Let's look at the code around the assertion in `getAddRecExpr`.                                                                               │
│ ```cpp                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ // llvm/lib/Analysis/ScalarEvolution.cpp                                                                                                                                                 │
│ const SCEV *ScalarEvolution::getAddRecExpr(                                                                                                                                              │
│     SmallVectorImpl<const SCEV *> &Operands, const Loop *L,                                                                                                                              │
│     SCEV::NoWrapFlags Flags) {                                                                                                                                                           │
│   // ...                                                                                                                                                                                 │
│   for (const SCEV *Op : Operands) {                                                                                                                                                      │
│     (void)Op;                                                                                                                                                                            │
│     assert(isAvailableAtLoopEntry(Op, L) &&                                                                                                                                              │
│            "SCEVAddRecExpr operand is not available at loop entry!");                                                                                                                    │
│   }                                                                                                                                                                                      │
│   // ...                                                                                                                                                                                 │
│ }                                                                                                                                                                                        │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
│ The `isAvailableAtLoopEntry` function is key.                                                                                                                                            │
│ ```cpp                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ // llvm/lib/Analysis/ScalarEvolution.cpp                                                                                                                                                 │
│ bool ScalarEvolution::isAvailableAtLoopEntry(const SCEV *S, const Loop *L) {                                                                                                             │
│   return isAvailableAt(S, L->getHeader()->getParent());                                                                                                                                  │
│ }                                                                                                                                                                                        │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
│ And `isAvailableAt`:                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ ```cpp                                                                                                                                                                                   │
